Costa Rica Coffee Exports Declined 22% Last Month, Icafe Says

-- B y   J o e   R i c h t e r
-- 
2011-09-01T17:58:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/costa-rica-coffee-exports-declined-22-last-month-icafe-says.html
Coffee exports from  Costa Rica  fell
22 percent in August, according to data from the Costa Rican
Coffee Institute, known as Icafe.  Shipments dropped to 34,302 bags from 43,715 bags in August
2010, data e-mailed by the institute showed today. Exports for
the first 11 months of the year that began Oct. 1 rose to 1.16
million bags from 1.14 million a year earlier, Icafe said. A bag
weighs 60 kilograms, or 132 pounds.  Costa Rica is ranked as Central Americaâ€™s fourth-largest
coffee producer for the 2010-2011 season, according to the
 International Coffee Organization .  To contact the reporter on this story:
